e app that you build in this collection of tutorials.\")","    }","    ","    @Chapter(name: \"SlothCreator Essentials\") {","        @Image(source: \"chapter1-slothcreatorEssentials.png\", alt: \"A wireframe of an app interface that has an outline of a sloth and four buttons below the sloth. The buttons display the following symbols, from left to right: snowflake, fire, wind, and lightning.\")","        ","        Create custom sloths and edit their attributes and powers using SlothCreator.","        ","        @TutorialReference(tutorial: \"doc:Creating-Custom-Sloths\")","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter to specify the name of your overall tutorial. This appears throughout the tutorial and in the tutorial’s URL when published on the web. Next, use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/DocC\/Intro"},{"type":"text","text":" directive to introduce the reader to your tutorial through engaging text and imagery. Then, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/DocC\/Chapter"},{"type":"text","text":" directives to reference the step-by-step pages. Chapters can also include images."}]},{"anchor":"Group-Related-Chapters","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Group Related Chapters"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/DocC\/Volume"},{"type":"text","text":" directive to group related chapters together if you need another level of organization. Volumes can also include images."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","code":["@Tutorials(name: \"SlothCreator\") {","    @Intro(title: \"Meet SlothCreator\") {","        ","        ...","    }","    ","    @Volume(name: \"Getting Started\") {","        Building sloths, caring for